The TFMP is a three-year program to modernize the conduct of field activities on tobacco production and this done by applying new technologies to increase farmers' efficiencies of labor utilization and increased productivity and income.  The program provides assistance in the form of technology and financial support in acquiring farm machineries and equipment with minimal interest of 2% per annum and one-time service fee of 1% to tobacco-based cooperatives/associations which  is payable in 3 to 10 years depending on the amount availed.  The cooperatives in turn can generate income through the rentals on the use of these equipment.

Objectives:
1. Provide financial support to farmers organizations in acquiring tractors and its accessories; 
2.  Provide income generation project for associations and cooperatives; 
3.  Increase the yield and net income of farmers; 
4.  Generate data/information which are essential in formulating policies for future projects of the same nature; 5.  Evaluate the technical and economic performance of the machineries.

